            {
              "id": "HEDGE-001",
              "name": "newMutatingEntryPointHasNoDetectedAuthenticationControl",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "New mutating entry point has no detected authentication control"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An unauthenticated actor may invoke a state-changing operation."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Only authenticated and authorized principals may invoke POST /api/files/upload.",
                "markdown": "### New mutating entry point has no detected authentication control\n\n**Security invariant:** Only authenticated and authorized principals may invoke POST /api/files/upload.\n\n**Attack path:** Public user → POST /api/files/upload → Privileged application operation\n\n**Missing controls:** Verified authentication, Authorization scoped to the target resource"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "architecture",
                  "threat-model",
                  "Spoofing",
                  "Elevation of Privilege"
                ],
                "precision": "high",
                "securitySeverity": "8.0",
                "cwe": [
                  "CWE-306"
                ],
                "stride": [
                  "Spoofing",
                  "Elevation of Privilege"
                ],
                "origin": "deterministic"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "HEDGE-002",
              "name": "newStorageWriteCrossesATrustBoundaryWithoutCompleteUploadControls",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "New storage write crosses a trust boundary without complete upload controls"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Unexpected content, oversized payloads, or cross-tenant object writes may reach privileged storage."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Uploaded content must be authenticated, tenant-scoped, type-checked, and bounded before storage.",
                "markdown": "### New storage write crosses a trust boundary without complete upload controls\n\n**Security invariant:** Uploaded content must be authenticated, tenant-scoped, type-checked, and bounded before storage.\n\n**Attack path:** External user → POST /api/files/upload → Storage write\n\n**Missing controls:** Verified authentication, Payload or file size limit, Object ownership constraint"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "architecture",
                  "threat-model",
                  "Tampering",
